  4. ARCHITECTURE & DESIGN PATTERNS

  4.1 Abstract Base Class Pattern

● Base Class: CipherAlgorithm (src/algorithms/base.py:4-61)

  The foundation of the entire cipher system. It uses Python's ABC (Abstract Base Class) module to enforce a
  contract that all cipher implementations must follow.

  Key Components:

  1. Abstract Methods (must be implemented by subclasses):
    - encrypt(text: str, key: Any) -> str - Encrypts plaintext
    - decrypt(text: str, key: Any) -> str - Decrypts ciphertext
    - validate_key(key: Any) -> bool - Validates key format
  2. Concrete Method (inherited by all):
    - clean_text(text: str) -> str - Converts to uppercase and removes spaces
  3. Instance Variable:
    - self.name - Automatically set to class name

  Why this design?:
  - Polymorphism: All ciphers can be treated uniformly
  - Contract enforcement: Python raises TypeError if abstract methods aren't implemented
  - Code reuse: Common functionality (text cleaning) is shared
  - Extensibility: New ciphers just inherit and implement 3 methods

