  7. UTILITY MODULES

  7.1 Text Processor (src/utils/text_processor.py)

  Purpose: Static utility class for text manipulation. No instance needed - all methods are @staticmethod.

  Methods:

  1. clean_for_encryption(text, preserve_spaces=False) (text_processor.py:7-28):
  # Without spaces: "Hello World!" → "HELLOWORLD"
  # With spaces: "Hello World!" → "HELLO WORLD"
  - Converts to uppercase
  - Uses regex re.sub(r'[^A-Z]', '', text) to remove non-letters
  - Optional space preservation for certain use cases

  2. format_output(text, block_size=5) (text_processor.py:31-44):
  # "HELLOWORLD" → "HELLO WORLD"
  # Custom size: format_output("ABCDEFGH", 3) → "ABC DEF GH"
  - Removes existing spaces
  - Splits into chunks: [text[i:i+block_size] for i in range(0, len(text), block_size)]
  - Joins with spaces for readability

  3. prepare_for_playfair(text) (text_processor.py:47-79):
  Specialized Playfair preparation:
  1. Clean text
  2. Replace J → I
  3. Separate duplicate pairs: "HELLO" → "HELXLO"
  4. Pad odd length with X

  4. restore_playfair_text(text) (text_processor.py:82-108):
  Attempts to reverse Playfair padding:
  - Removes trailing X
  - Removes X between duplicate letters
  - Note: Imperfect - can't distinguish padding X from legitimate X

