● 10. EXECUTION WORKFLOWS

  10.1 Import Path Management

  Challenge: Tests need to import from src/, but Python doesn't know about parent directories.

  Solution (used in ALL test files and interfaces):
  import sys
  import os

  # Calculate parent directory
  sys.path.append(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))

  Breakdown:
  - __file__ = current file path (e.g., /tests/test_caesar.py)
  - os.path.abspath(__file__) = absolute path
  - os.path.dirname(...) = parent directory
  - Second dirname = grandparent (project root)
  - sys.path.append(...) = add to Python's import search path

  After this: Can use from src.algorithms.caesar import CaesarCipher

